{"id":"aholiab","term":"Aholiab","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Tent of the father, an artist of the tribe of Dan, appointed to the work of preparing materials for the tabernacle (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 31:6\">Ex. 31:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 35:34\">35:34</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 36:1\">36:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 36:2\">2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 38:23\">38:23</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Exodus 31:6","Exodus 35:34","Exodus 36:1","Exodus 36:2","Exodus 38:23"]}